<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1926,2033]" box="[198,921,1926,1953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Description.</emphasis>
MALE. Lengths: Body: 
<quantity box="[644,737,1927,1953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
; wing: 
<quantity box="[823,917,1927,1953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1926,2033]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,418]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Head</emphasis>
. Vertex and occiput yellowish brown with fairly dense small black recumbent hairs. Frons obscurely yellow. Antennae: scape and pedicel cup-shaped, obscurely yellow. Flagellum: segment I obscurely yellow; remaining segments dark brown. Face yellow. Palpi: segments I–II yellowish brown, segments III–IV pale brown; segment IV long and slender. Labellum yellowish brown, fleshy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum yellowish brown with yellow on humeral area and side margins; long dark setae on side margins. Scutellum yellowish brown with long setae on posterior margin. Prothorax yellow with some long setae. Anepisternum pale brown, bare; katepisternum anteroventrally yellowish brown, remainder of katepisternum yellow. Laterotergite and mediotergite yellowish brown, bare. Halter yellow, knob yellow with brown dorsally.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176549/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" targetBox="[267,1355,462,1680]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1701,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,325,1701,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">FIGURES 4–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[333,501,1702,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Xenoplatyura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[333,501,1702,1725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">X. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[516,578,1701,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[516,578,1701,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
4. gonocoxites and gonostyli, ventral view. 5. male terminalia, lateral view. 6. tergite IX and cercus, dorsal view. 7. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1811,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,256,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Legs</emphasis>
. Yellow. Fore coxa, apex of mid and hind coxae with long recumbent black hairs. Femora with recumbent black hairs. Fore and mid tibiae with setulae in rows on apical half, hind tibia with setulae in rows on apical third. All tibiae with some setae. Fore tibia without comb, mid tibia with posterior comb and hind tibia with anterior and posterior combs. Tibial spurs dark brown. Fore and mid basitarsi subequal in length to lengths of their respective tibiae, hind basitarsus 
<number box="[723,760,1971,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" value="0.7">0.7</number>
x length of hind tibia. Claws minute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,347,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,823,1827]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[415,1171,1165,1492]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Xenoplatyura wings. 1. X. sichuanensis, n. sp. 2. X. lata, n. sp. 3. X. bifida, n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176548/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[333,347,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with faint infuscation discernible below tip of R 
<number box="[1037,1052,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="5.0">5</number>
. Veins dark brown. Costa almost reaching one-third distance from vein R 
<number box="[623,636,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="5.0">5</number>
to vein M 
<number box="[764,774,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[792,808,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="2.0">2</number>
; Sc ends slightly beyond base of Rs; Sc-R situated at level of basal 
<number box="[316,404,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3</number>
of distance between h and tip of Sc. Distance between tips of R 
<number box="[1165,1175,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1254,1268,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
<number box="[1276,1365,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.7000000000000002" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8</number>
times as long as R 
<number box="[298,314,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
. Ratio of radiomedial fusion / petiole of M: 
<number box="[836,928,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="0.55" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.6</number>
. Petiole of M one-fifth as long as length of M 
<number box="[182,192,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[210,226,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="2.0">2</number>
. Veins M 
<number box="[336,350,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="2.0">2</number>
and CuA 
<number box="[468,477,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
not reaching wing margin, vein A reaches wing margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites I–VI obscurely yellow, tergites VII–VIII yellowish brown; all of the tergites with dense recumbent black hairs. Sternum patterned as on tergites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[372,489,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7. X" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[267,1355,462,1680]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. X. sichuanensis, n. sp. 4. gonocoxites and gonostyli, ventral view. 5. male terminalia, lateral view. 6. tergite IX and cercus, dorsal view. 7. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176549/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Figs. 
<number box="[441,489,432,458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[654,770,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7. X" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[267,1355,462,1680]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. X. sichuanensis, n. sp. 4. gonocoxites and gonostyli, ventral view. 5. male terminalia, lateral view. 6. tergite IX and cercus, dorsal view. 7. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176549/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
) brown, broad and slightly elongated; cercus visible in dorsal view. Genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[476,617,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7. X" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[267,1355,462,1680]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. X. sichuanensis, n. sp. 4. gonocoxites and gonostyli, ventral view. 5. male terminalia, lateral view. 6. tergite IX and cercus, dorsal view. 7. aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/176549/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
Figs. 4, 5, 
<number box="[599,617,472,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
